docs.lead_paragraph: In a story Sept. 29 about a former Florida sheriff's deputy accused of using a stun gun on a woman, The Associated Press reported erroneously details about a cake reading "Sorry I Tased You." The woman's attorney says the deputy sent a photo of the cake, made by someone else, to the woman; the deputy did not bake the cake himself, as stated in the lawsuit.
